READ FIRST: SURFACE_CONTRACT.md in repo root. Surface is modeled as a slime: shape-free (UI/API/MCP/bot/dashboard/wizard/anything), invariants-bound.

ABSOLUTE rule #0 (Yggdrasil scope vs Backend scope):
- Yggdrasil (including surfaces) = IDP for the operating COMPANY's internal team (collaborators, devops, platform engineers, ops).
- Backend services = end-user-facing business operations (customers, consumers).
- A surface views/dispatches company-owned resources for the internal team — never an end-user product frontend.
- Example: "Stripe webhook health dashboard for platform team" = Yggdrasil surface. "Pay your bill" page for customers = NOT Yggdrasil (operator product frontend).
- Heuristic: audience is COMPANY internal team → Yggdrasil; audience is END-USERS → not Yggdrasil.

Invariants every surface honors:
- Stateless w.r.t. business state (strongly discouraged with ADR exception path).
- Auth via Yggdrasil session (delegated; never reimplement).
- Backend-agnostic: calls Yggdrasil core API; direct provider bypass strongly discouraged.
- Multi-tenant aware: integration_instance scoping respected.
- Lego principle: no hardcoded cloud / CDN / auth / analytics / i18n provider.
- No business decisions.

Hard line (no exceptions):
- NEVER log credentials, secrets, tokens.
- NEVER reimplement user auth from scratch.
- NEVER hardcode a specific cloud / CDN / hosting / auth provider.
- NEVER make business decisions.

Freedoms (slime adapts):
- Any framework, any shape, any real-time mechanism.
- UX-edge persistence (localStorage, IndexedDB) for non-business state.
- Custom data shaping, aggregations, cross-integration composition.
- New surface "shapes" don't need permission — invariants do.

This repository is the official Yggdrasil surface template. Keep it generic, core-first, production-friendly. Preserve readiness and shutdown defaults.
